President Donald Trump issued a proclamation declaring November 1, 2020, as a National Day of Remembrance for Americans Killed by Illegal Aliens. The proclamation honors the memory of American lives lost to criminal illegal aliens and expresses support for their families, known as Angel Families. The President pledges to ensure justice for these tragedies and to take action to prevent future acts of violence by securing the border and enforcing immigration laws. The proclamation highlights the creation of the Victims Of Immigration Crime Engagement (VOICE) office, which provides assistance to affected families. It also emphasizes the efforts to construct a border wall, end catch-and-release policies, deploy National Guard personnel, and deport criminal illegal aliens. The President asserts that these actions are saving American lives, curbing crime, and protecting communities. The proclamation calls on the people of the United States to observe the National Day of Remembrance with appropriate ceremonies and activities.